programme.title: The Fedora
programme.desc: Can the fedora be cool again? Kyle Ng meets up with the people at the heart of hat culture to find out. As popular as it is divisive, the fedora is a controversial accessory. Kyle Ng explores the Pachuco culture, meets a celebrity hatmaker, and travels to the United Kingdom to run with the Rude Boys, all to find out more about the infamous headwear.

programme.title: The Blue Armada
programme.desc: An award-winning Russian motorsports team show their unique way of working and preparing for the Dakar Rally. The most famous and award-winning motorsports team in Russia use their unique way of working together to prepare for off-road racing's most prestigious event, the Dakar Rally.

programme.title: The Silent Samurai
programme.sub-title: A look back at Dani Pedrosa's career
programme.desc: Take a look at the key moments that made Dani Pedrosa one of the most talented riders of his generation. Enjoy a look back at Dani Pedrosa’s motorcycling career as seen through the eyes of his coach, friend and former MotoGP star Sete Gibernau. Relive the key moments that made him one of the most talented riders of his generation.

programme.title: Rich + Tone: PolyRhythmic
programme.desc: Choreography team Rich + Tone take it back to their roots as they talk about their career in the dance world. Brothers Richmond and Anthony Talauega have been behind some of pop music's most explosive dance performances. Their inspiration for dancing comes from their heritage and upbringing, which they revisit as they craft a major routine for Chris Brown.

programme.title: What Lies Ahead
programme.desc: The b-boys consider their futures. Roxrite judges a competition. Neguin visits friends. Lilou makes a choice. The b-boys get honest with themselves while setting their future goals. Roxrite judges a BC One qualifier. Neguin takes his nephew to an open b-boy practice session. After some soul-searching, Lilou opts to go for a third world championship.

programme.title: The Learning Curve
programme.sub-title: Drew Bezanson: From BMX to MTB
programme.desc: Drew Bezanson tries to make the transition from freestyle BMX to the world of slopestyle mountain biking. To be a master of two sports is a feat many have tried but few have accomplished. Drew Bezanson is one of the top BMX riders in the world, but now he wants to enter the world of slopestyle mountain biking and compete at Red Bull Joyride.

programme.title: Wingmen
programme.desc: Three elite BASE jumpers face the unknown on a global journey to find the best wingsuit and BASE jump spots. Three of the world's best wingsuit flyers set out on a global journey in search of perfect spots for proximity flying and BASE jumps. From Brazil to China, the trio face some of the most thrilling and challenging flights of their lives.

programme.title: Turn up in Tahiti
programme.desc: The whole crew take off from Maui and head to Teahupo'o, Tahiti, where they immediately hit the waves. The whole crew take off from Maui and head to Teahupo'o, Tahiti, where they immediately hit the waves despite the rain. Then it's time for another round of Poopies riding his way down a mountainside.

programme.title: Red Bull Music Studio Sessions: Kelly Rowland
programme.desc: Kelly Rowland and producers collaborate to share an artistic journey of music writing and recording. Go behind the scenes of a creative musical journey as a team of songwriters and producers write and record three tracks with superstar singer and artist Kelly Rowland at Red Bull Studios Los Angeles.

programme.title: King of the Peak
programme.sub-title: Driving the historic Pikes Peak course
programme.desc: Two drivers attempt to break the world record time at the Pikes Peak International Hill Climb, Colorado, USA. The Pikes Peak International Hill Climb, Colorado, USA – a 19.99km (12.4 mile), 156-turn monster of a track – has been pushing drivers to the limit since 1916. In 2013 Rhys Millen and Sébastien Loeb tried to set a record time at this historic race.

programme.title: Rob Meets Sam Sunderland
programme.desc: Rob Warner meets 2017 Dakar Rally winner Sam Sunderland as he hones his motorcycle skills for the 2019 event. Rob Warner heads to France to meet with 2017 Dakar Rally winner Sam Sunderland to see how the British motorcycle rider’s preparations are going for the 2019 edition of the event.

programme.title: Game Loading
programme.desc: Disrupting the big-budget games industry, indie developers have forever impacted the world of video games. Explore the world of indie game developers – their craft, their games, their dreams and the way that these small teams of artists and programmers have forever changed not only video game culture, but the world at large.

programme.title: Rebound
programme.desc: With a major tournament on the horizon, can Leffen recover from a disappointing EGLX showing in Canada? After a disappointing seventh place finish at the EGLX tournament, Leffen must rediscover the mindset that once made him a Melee winner. The first step: lots of practice with top competition to prepare for the upcoming GOML 2016 tournament.

programme.title: Reclaim
programme.desc: Leffen finds himself in Winners Semis at GOML 2016 against one of the best players in Melee history: Armada. Leffen finds himself in Winners Semis at GOML 2016 but is up against one of the most dominant players in Melee history: Armada. Can Leffen rediscover the elite form needed to win and reclaim his place among the gods of Melee?

programme.title: Ready, Aim, Skate
programme.desc: Ryan, David, and Kane head from Albuquerque to Denver, where they get to do some shooting before filming. Ryan, David, and Kane spend their final hours in Albuquerque filming party lines before hitting the road to David's hometown of Denver. The Mile High City gives them buttery ledges, smooth rails, and a shooting excursion with Dagger 8 Armory.

programme.title: Age of Ondra part 1
programme.desc: Czech Republic's Adam Ondra has set out to be the best climber in every aspect, and he has achieved that. Czech Republic's Adam Ondra has set out to be the best climber in every aspect, and he has achieved that. Get inside Ondra's mind to find out what has fuelled him from such a young age.

programme.title: Pressure Drop
programme.desc: Brandon Semenuk goes for the ride of his life as he attempts to film his part for unReal in one shot. In an attempt to put his stamp on boundary-pushing videos, freeride mountain bike superstar Brandon Semenuk attempts to film his whole segment for unReal in a single take. Battling the clock and the odds, he has one shot to make history.
